Visualizations

Station usage

The following plots depict the number of trips that started from and ended at each of the current Citi Bike stations, for January and March of 2017.

Starting station

There was little difference between station usage in the two months. The most trips started at Pershing Square North, which is located right next to Grand Central Station. There were 7683 trips starting from this station in January and 8081 trips in March.



Terminal station

The station where the most trips ended was also Pershing Square North. In January, 7744 trips ended at this station, and 7971 trips ended here in March.




Rider characteristics

Gender and age

In the months analyzed, there were significantly more rides by males compared to females. There were a total of 824,539 rides taken by male riders and 250,221 rides taken by female riders.

The average age of a male rider was 40.12 years, and `39.01 years for female riders. The oldest male rider was 99 years old, and the oldest female rider was 96 years old.
